        "text": "Probably no region in the world and no historical epoch is better suited to study the logic of war as an ideal type than the society of the Fiji Islands in the 19th century. At that time, there were enough observers from Europe who could describe the events and processes with sufficient emotional and intellectual distance, but the European influence was not yet so great in its colonizing and missionary effect that it would have fundamentally changed conditions."
      },
      "date": 1708668726075
